data.content:
Here's what breaks in EF Core 10 and the fixes:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer accepts expression trees

**What broke:** The overload now takes `Func<...>` instead of `Expression<Func<...>>`. Your manual expression-tree code won't compile.

**Fix — replace with simple imperative code:**

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

## 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified / nested paths changed

**What broke:**
- `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared the column `Street`; now EF appends a number (e.g. `Street1`) to avoid collisions.
- Nested complex types now use the **full path**: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` → column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was just `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix — pin the old column names explicitly:**

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// Nested: pin the old shorter name
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

Or generate a new migration and apply the renames if you prefer the new convention.

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

**What broke:** Every method gained a mandatory `string logCommandText` parameter; your class no longer compiles.

**Fix:**

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← add this
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants are redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the real SQL
    }
}
```

Add the same parameter to all other methods (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
